node.text:
Peace 
--------------------------------------------
#mykindoftimelapse
Shot this type of timelapse for the first time . I thought capturing a timelapse is really hard and time consuming but after capturing this video (after 4 tries) it turns out to be it is really pleasing , relaxing and joyful.
.
Ps. Shooting a timelapse and the cool breeze at terrace lost my headache too 
.
P.ps. this was shot on nikon d5600 with settings 5 second interval for 15 minutes . 
.
You can shoot timelapse on any device just give it a try ✌🏻
.
Do tell me in comment section how was this first try and should I come up with more different timelapse 😉
----------------------------------------------

node.text:
Kedarnath trek 
Almost one year ago I went to kedar trek with my family . Initially I went just because of my parent's 'do dham yatra' but it turns out to be my one of the best and favourite trip. 
Not only I saw some beautiful valleys but 
1. Saw how real camping is ( sleeping in sleep bag, how food was served, and finding clean washroom 😅)
2. First time in life saw shooting star and galaxy's arm through naked eyes
3. Funny incident of me falling from mule ( खच्चर ) 
4. First time enjoyed other people's culture
5. Bathing in icy chilled but purest water in mandakini river
6. Inhaling pure air as no motor vehicle was there
7. Taking first time pic of any baba ( photo me jo baba hai wo camera dekhte hi pose kar dete the 😂)
.
Whenever I see these pics a smile comes on my face automatically. .
Hope you enjoyed reading that 😊✌🏻.
.
Ps. This trip made me landscape, portrait,street and astro photographer in just two weeks of buying a dslr 😅😂.
.
P.ps. do comment which pic do you liked the most ? or how was the story telling , do you enjoyed that ?
